main event: A pin point of white light was observed above the horizon on 25 Oct 63.
interesting points: The white light was seen traveling from north to south., Visual contact was lost when the object reached 60 degrees above the horizon., The observation was at a location with coordinates 42°35'N 174°50'W in the Pacific., The report concluded that the sighted object was likely a satellite., The information was retransmitted to the CIA.
sighted object: a pin point of white light
